1) Check out the code
    $ mkdir workspace 
    $ cd workspace
    $ git clone https://github.com/saga-project/DARE/tree/master/gateways/DARE-BIGJOB

2) Create virtualenv
    $ virtualenv /tmp/envdare
    $ source /tmp/envdae/bin/activate
    
3) INSTALL DARE-BIGJOB Env.
    $ cd DARE-BIGJOB/
    $ pip install -r requirements.txt
    
4) create/sync/update Database schema
    $ python manage.py syncdb
    $ python manage.py migrate

5) Running the django web server
    $ python manage.py runserver




Useful links:
    1) South for data schema migrations. http://south.readthedocs.org/en/0.7.6/
    2) Django Celery for asynchronous tasks from webserver. http://docs.celeryproject.org/en/latest/getting-started/first-steps-with-celery.html
    3) django-social-auth for login with google. https://github.com/omab/django-social-auth
    4) django-picklefield for storing serialized objects. https://pypi.python.org/pypi/django-picklefield
    5) django compressor for compressing javascript and css files to serve on the web. https://github.com/jezdez/django_compressor
    6) django-extensions for command line operations like django-shell. https://github.com/django-extensions/django-extensions